<br>
SA = Secondary Assist, just like the Main Assist, but is the person who steps in to be the MA should the MA go LD, die in ways best left unsaid or snap due to long simmiering metal problems.<br>
<br>
TM = Tank Mezz, this is the luckless tank who is given the job of entertaining mobs that can't me mezzed by the Chanters or Bards.  They keep the extra mobs angry at them and away from all the silk wearing snacks till the mob the MA has chosen is dead.<br>
<br>
Puller = The person who runs out and brings things to kill, hopefully in small enough numbers so as to not over whelm the raid.<br>
<br>
Tagger = This is often, but not nessarily the MA also.  This is the person, and the only person who gets agro from a mob that a puller has brought to a point where they have either FD'ed or been killed.  The Taggers job is to make sure that no more then the intend number of critters are brought in.<br>
<br>
Assist Key = This is why all the above is important, on raids it is very important to know who each of these people are.  Never attack anything unless one of the assists has targeted it first.  Always assist the MA or SA, not the TM.<br>
An assist key is made like this:<br>
/assist <name of MA><br>
/assist <name of SA><br>
<br>
All melee on a raid should have these two keys to make sure we are all killing the same thing at the same time.<br>
If there is any doubt as to who is who, please ask, it is far, far better to repeat this information then to lose a fight because all the enchanters die to broken mezzes.<br>
<br>
